item.title: Queen Elizabeth's Coffin Adorned by Orb and Sceptre: Details
item.description: Symbolic artifacts. The Sovereign’s Orb and the Sovereign’s Sceptre With Cross will be placed on top of the casket. The orb is presented to British monarchs during their coronation. Dating back to Charles II’s coronation in 1661, the piece of regalia is golden and has a cross perched on top to symbolize heavenly power over the world.

The practice doesn’t just extend to remaking the same movie again and again — it also encompasses classic films being turned into television series. Casablanca, for example, winner of the 1943 Oscar for Best Picture, spawned two short-lived TV adaptions. The first show, titled Casablanca, premiered on ABC in 1955 but was canceled after 10 episodes.
